Nigerian government on Thursday ordered the immediate suspension of the proposed Unstructured Supplementary Service Data (USSD) charges on customers who uses them. “After receiving briefing about the proposed USSD charges, I realized there was no justification for the new tariff,” minister of communication Dr Isa Ali Ibrahim Pantami said. “Consequently, I directed it’s immediate suspension, any telecom operator that violates this directive would be sanctioned appropriately.” To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .